low where the browser sends user requests to the web application and receives responses.\\n\\n- **Connections Between Web Application and Routing Microservice**: \\n   - Data flow where the web application forwards requests to the routing microservice, and receives response data to relay back to the browser.\\n\\n- **Connections Between Routing Microservice and Other Microservices**:\\n   - The routing microservice directs requests to the Search, NonSearch, and Conversational microservices as required, highlighting a dynamic interaction based on request type.\\n\\n- **Connections to Azure Cognitive Search and OpenAI Models**:\\n   - Microservices send requests to the Azure Cognitive Search and the OpenAI models for processing and receive results back, illustrating integration with cloud-based services:\\n      - Search Microservice to Azure Cognitive Search;\\n      - NonSearch Microservice and Conversational Microservice to Azure OpenAI GPT 3.5 Model;\\n      -  Web Application to Azure OpenAI Text Moderation Model.\\n\\n- **Connections Between Azure Cognitive Search, OpenAI models and Azure Monitor**:\\n    - Data flow where the Azure Monitor collects performance and health metrics from the OpenAI models and Azure Cognitive Search.\\n\\n### Trust Boundaries:\\n\\n1. **ABC Mart On-Premise Network Boundary**: \\n   - This boundary separates the internal network infrastructure of ABC Mart from the external world (users accessing the web application). Communication across this boundary must ensure secure interactions.\\n\\n2. **Azure Cloud Trust Boundary**: \\n   - Represents the separation between on-premise operations and Azure cloud services. Ensures that data exchanged with Azure Cognitive Search and OpenAI models is secure and compliant with privacy standards.\\n\\nThis text describes each component in the DFD by categorizing them and outlining the connections between them.\"",
